2533882\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 13, 2022</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104xry1665702988946.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/xry1665702988946.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/xry1665702988946.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"xry1665702988946\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Decimal and Octal Character Values\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"xry1665702988946__decimal_and_octal_character_values_193966\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Decimal or octal values allow you to define special characters.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"xry1665702988946__topic_d64634e1_d64635e1_d64636e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xry1665702988946__p_d64637e1_d64638e1_d64639e1\">Decimal Values: <code class=\"ph codeph\">^<var class=\"keyword varname\">nnn</var>\n</code>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xry1665702988946__p_d64640e1_d64641e1_d64642e1\">Octal Values: <code class=\"ph codeph\">^/<var class=\"keyword varname\">nnn</var>\n</code>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"xry1665702988946__topic_d42742e1_d42743e1_d42744e1_d42745e1_d42746e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d268288e74\">\n                     \n Arguments\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xry1665702988946__p_d64646e1_d64647e1_d64648e1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">nnn</var>—up to three digits:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"xry1665702988946__li_d28082e1_d28083e1_d28084e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xry1665702988946__p_d64649e1_d64650e1_d64651e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">000</code> through <code class=\"ph codeph\">255</code> for decimal values</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"xry1665702988946__li_d28085e1_d28086e1_d28087e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xry1665702988946__p_d64652e1_d64653e1_d64654e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">000</code> through <code class=\"ph codeph\">377</code> for octal values</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"xry1665702988946__topic_d42747e1_d42748e1_d42749e1_d42750e1_d42751e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d268288e113\">\n                     \n Description\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xry1665702988946__p_d64658e1_d64659e1_d64660e1\">If a mnemonic for a character is not available, or if you prefer to do it this way, you can enter the decimal or octal value for each character.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xry1665702988946__p_d64661e1_d64662e1_d64663e1\">It is not possible to enter anything other than Uniface Font 0 characters in a translation table, so using decimal or octal values allows you to define special characters. Specific definitions of special characters should always use this syntax.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xry1665702988946__p_d64664e1_d64665e1_d64666e1\">For example, both <code class=\"ph codeph\">^66</code> and <code class=\"ph codeph\">^/102</code> are interpreted as the ASCII character <code class=\"ph codeph\">B</code>.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533882\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533882\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Decimal and Octal Character Values Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 13, 2022 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Decimal and Octal Character Values Decimal or octal values allow you to define special characters. Decimal Values: ^ nnn Octal Values: ^/ nnn Arguments nnn —up to three digits: 000 through 255 for decimal values 000 through 377 for octal values Description If a mnemonic for a character is not available, or if you prefer to do it this way, you can enter the decimal or octal value for each character. It is not possible to enter anything other than Uniface Font 0 characters in a translation table, so using decimal or octal values allows you to define special characters. Specific definitions of special characters should always use this syntax. For example, both ^66 and ^/102 are interpreted as the ASCII character B . Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}